The White House Press Secretary, Jay Carney, gave a press briefing on January 8, 2013. During the briefing, Carney discussed a variety of topics including the nomination of John Brennan to be CIA director, the debt ceiling, gun control, and the potential for a government shutdown. Carney also addressed the issue of the fiscal cliff and the ongoing negotiations between the President and Congress. Additionally, he commented on the possibility of a new Palestinian state and the future of US aid to Egypt and Pakistan. Finally, Carney briefly mentioned the situation in France with Gerard Depardieu and the upcoming Supreme Court case on gay marriage.